@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>At [Company Name], we value your privacy and are committed to safeguarding the personal information of our users. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your information when you use our Task Management Web App. By using the App, you consent to the practices described in this policy.</p>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect the following types of information to provide and improve our services:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Identification Information:</strong> When you sign up or log in, we collect personal information such as your name, email address, and job title.</li>
        <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Users may input personal and professional information related to their tasks, including deadlines, project details, and communication preferences.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We collect usage data, such as your interactions with the App, task assignments, updates, and navigation activities.</li>
        <li><strong>Role-Specific Data:</strong> Depending on your role (Employee, Task Manager, Administrator), different access levels and functionalities are available. We collect and store data related to tasks assigned, completed, and tracked.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>To Provide Services:</strong> To create, manage, and track tasks and projects based on your role.</li>
        <li><strong>To Improve the App:</strong> To analyze usage patterns and enhance the features and functionality of the App.</li>
        <li><strong>For Communication:</strong> To send updates about tasks, deadlines, and system notifications relevant to your role.</li>
        <li><strong>Security and Account Management:</strong> To ensure proper access control and safeguard your account information.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We will not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> We may share your data with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the App, processing payments, or conducting analysis. These providers are contractually obligated to protect your data.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to legal processes, such as a subpoena or government request.</li>
        <li><strong>To Protect Rights:</strong> If necessary, we may share information to protect our rights, the rights of our users, or the security of the App.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>4. User Roles and Data Access</h2>
    <p>The App supports different roles with varying access levels:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Employee:</strong> Employees can view and manage their assigned tasks, update task progress, and communicate within their designated projects. They only have access to their own task data.</li>
        <li><strong>Task Manager:</strong> Task Managers have access to tasks across multiple employees and teams, allowing them to assign, edit, and monitor tasks. They can view employee progress and performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Administrator:</strong> Administrators have the highest level of access and can manage users, configure App settings, and view all tasks, users, and data associated with the App.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your personal information and data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. If you delete your account, we will make reasonable efforts to remove your information, but some residual data may be retained for legal or operational reasons.</p>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your personal data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction. These include encryption, access controls, and secure communication protocols. However, no method of data transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.</p>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Access and Update:</strong> You can access and update your personal information through the App. If you need assistance, please contact our support team.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Deletion:</strong> You may request the deletion of your account or personal data at any time. Please note that some data may be retained for legal reasons.</li>
        <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> You may opt-out of receiving marketing communications or notifications at any time by adjusting your settings or contacting support.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>8. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
    <p>The App may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these external sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before sharing any personal information.</p>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>9. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>The App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected data from a child, please contact us immediately, and we will take steps to remove it.</p>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will post the updated policy on this page with a new effective date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about our data practices.</p>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
    <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:</p>
    <p>
        <strong>[Company Name]</strong><br>
        [Company Address]<br>
        [Phone Number]<br>
        [Email Address]
    </p>
</div>

